<subSubSection id="D7DA68FEFFE6E87FFF51E322FEC7A1CA" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9F7F3B75FFE6E87FFF51E322FEC7A1CA" blockId="22.[151,1127,1331,1451]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis id="ADB4E767FFE6E87FFF51E322FEC4A12A" bold="true" box="[151,298,1331,1355]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425">Distribution.</emphasis>
A species occurring in India (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE6E87FFD5CE322FCC2A12A" author="MAULIK S." box="[666,812,1331,1355]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" refId="ref13919" refString="MAULIK S. 1936: The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae). Taylor and Francis, London, xv + 648 pp." type="book" year="1936">MAULIK 1936</bibRefCitation>
), Nepal (
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE6E87FFC4BE322FBDAA12A" author="TAKIZAWA H." box="[909,1076,1331,1355]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" pagination="275 - 291" refId="ref14247" refString="TAKIZAWA H. 1990: Chrysomelid beetles of Nepal, Northeastern India and Western Sikkim collected by the Himalaya expeditions of the National Science Museum, Tokyo (Part 2). Japanese Journal of Entomology 58: 275 - 291." type="journal article" year="1990">TAKIZAWA 1990</bibRefCitation>
), Sri Lanka (
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE6E87FFF2EE342FE50A10A" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S." box="[232,446,1363,1387]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref14001" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. 1997: The galerucine beetles of Sri Lanka, with descriptions of two new species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Stobaeana 9: 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1997">MOHAMEDSAID 1997</bibRefCitation>
), and Socotra Island (present paper). Recorded also from Sudan (
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE6E87FFF59E362FEB4A1EA" author="LABOISSIERE V." box="[159,346,1395,1419]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" pagination="190 - 193" refId="ref13843" refString="LABOISSIERE V. 1926: Description d'un nouveau genre et de trois nouvelles especes de Galerucini africains (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 1926: 190 - 193." type="journal article" year="1926">LABOISSIÈRE 1926</bibRefCitation>
) under the name 
<taxonomicName id="58C040F6FFE6E87FFDD3E365FC3DA1EA" authority="Laboissiere, 1926" authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1926" box="[533,979,1395,1419]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Neorudolphia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bedfordi">
<emphasis id="ADB4E767FFE6E87FFDD3E365FCE4A1EA" box="[533,778,1396,1419]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="425">Neorudolphia bedfordi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE6E87FFCD7E362FC3DA1EA" author="LABOISSIERE V." box="[785,979,1395,1419]" pageId="22" pageNumber="425" pagination="190 - 193" refId="ref13843" refString="LABOISSIERE V. 1926: Description d'un nouveau genre et de trois nouvelles especes de Galerucini africains (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 1926: 190 - 193." type="journal article" year="1926">Laboissière, 1926</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="ADB4E767FFE6E87FFC1BE362FEC7A1CA" bold="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="425">
First record from 
<collectingCountry id="E7D77BE5FFE6E87FFF13E382FECAA1CA" box="[213,292,1427,1451]" name="Yemen" pageId="22" pageNumber="425">Yemen</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
